   "source": [
    "# `ibip`\n",
    "Image based invasion percolation algorithm to simulate volume controlled injection of non-wetting fluid into an image"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "a9d1c241",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:55:54.419612Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:55:54.419270Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:55:56.608449Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:55:56.607838Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import porespy as ps\n",
    "ps.visualization.set_mpl_style()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4534e449",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The arguments and their defaults are:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "6b71d2bc",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:55:56.611332Z",

     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:55:56.616981Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:55:56.616395Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<Signature (im, inlets=None, dt=None, maxiter=10000)>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import inspect\n",
    "inspect.signature(ps.filters.ibip)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "be7c7aa2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

    "Can be a 2D or 3D image:"
   ]

   "source": [
    "im = ps.generators.blobs(shape=[200, 200], porosity=0.7, blobiness=0.75)\n",
    "ip = ps.filters.ibip(im=im)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[12, 6])\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(ip.inv_sequence/im, origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(ip.inv_sizes/im, origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "96ccc4cc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The function results a ``Results`` object with an image containing the invasion sequence of each voxel (left) and the invasion size of each voxel (right).  These can be used to generate a capillary pressure curve."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "35771334",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   "source": [
    "inlets = np.zeros_like(im)\n",
    "inlets[0, ...] = True\n",
    "ip = ps.filters.ibip(im=im, inlets=inlets)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[12, 6])\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(ip.inv_sequence/im, origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(ip.inv_sizes/im, origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False);"
   ]
  },
